The paper proposes a new architecture for recurrent neural networks, specifically echo state networks, to solve complex and multiple timescale temporal tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of intrinsic plasticity, which is a form of unsupervised learning, indicating that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The proposed architecture is designed to solve temporal tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions time series prediction tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
